gomodel:SYNGO_4984  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: Figure 4: using light microscopy and software assistance to categorized and count dendritic spines, authors observed that NgR1 (Nogo receptor-1, gene RTN4R) overexpression limits the number of mature mushroom spines in-vivo in neurons from frontal association cortex, the cingulate cortex, and nucleus accumbens regions of mouse brains.. Experimental description: result text: \"In the frontal association cortex, we found that the apical dendrites of pyramidal neurons had significantly lower spine densities in NgR1 overexpressing mice compared with control mice (Fig. 4A, genotype P = 0.003).\"" ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-4973-5732" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2514-0216" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2286-1587" ;
        dc:date           "2023-02-08" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_BP_4984" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_10090" .

